153
00:15:39,560 --> 00:15:40,080
[SPEAKER_11]: Good evening.

154
00:15:41,261 --> 00:15:42,362
[SPEAKER_11]: Let's talk about your site.

155
00:15:43,183 --> 00:15:59,577
[SPEAKER_11]: So a little history back in 1967, to allow for the building of this high school, there was a land swap done between the Metropolitan District Commission, that is now known as DCR, Department of Conservation Resources, and Mississippi.

156
00:16:00,484 --> 00:16:05,508
[SPEAKER_11]: So in that deal, there were swapping of various parcels, which you'll see in the next slide.

157
00:16:06,909 --> 00:16:15,136
[SPEAKER_11]: And along with those parcels that were conveyed by, say, now DCR, there were some restrictions on use.

158
00:16:15,236 --> 00:16:18,438
[SPEAKER_11]: What could be done on those pieces of land?

159
00:16:18,999 --> 00:16:20,560
[SPEAKER_11]: Specifically, no buildings.

160
00:16:21,141 --> 00:16:27,546
[SPEAKER_11]: They were meant to be held for athletics and recreation, which is DCR's mission.

161
00:16:28,640 --> 00:16:34,766
[SPEAKER_11]: Um, that restriction does have a 999 year term to it.

162
00:16:34,886 --> 00:16:39,289
[SPEAKER_11]: And if you can do the math in your head, add it to 1967.

163
00:16:39,510 --> 00:16:44,014
[SPEAKER_11]: And so we've got some challenges with the site as we now know.

164
00:16:44,774 --> 00:16:45,195
[SPEAKER_11]: The next.

165
00:16:46,836 --> 00:16:54,543
[SPEAKER_11]: So the green highlighted areas are the parcels that were conveyed by DCR to the city.

166
00:16:55,564 --> 00:16:55,664
[SPEAKER_11]: Um,

167
00:16:57,307 --> 00:17:03,331
[SPEAKER_11]: The city gate to DCR is not really highlighted, but it is to the northeast.

168
00:17:03,872 --> 00:17:09,636
[SPEAKER_11]: And again, those are areas that are restricted from building buildings into that.

169
00:17:11,078 --> 00:17:20,805
[SPEAKER_11]: As part of the feasibility study, the team did bring on a land survey team, and many of you talked about the survey quite a bit.

170
00:17:21,686 --> 00:17:24,208
[SPEAKER_11]: It was a tremendous undertaking.

171
00:17:24,862 --> 00:17:35,650
[SPEAKER_11]: more than four months of work that included both research, a ton of field work, and then a lot of confirming work.

172
00:17:35,670 --> 00:17:44,477
[SPEAKER_11]: And what happens in the early part when they started onto the project back in November, they pulled all of the information and they started with the plans.

173
00:17:44,957 --> 00:17:53,584
[SPEAKER_11]: The plans helped them map out a way to approach the field work, which again took months of time.

174
00:17:54,280 --> 00:18:02,325
[SPEAKER_11]: Those plans help them to locate monumentation and do all of the drone work, the field work, etc.

175
00:18:02,345 --> 00:18:07,208
[SPEAKER_11]: A draft survey was provided to us in February.

176
00:18:08,818 --> 00:18:12,821
[SPEAKER_11]: And once that work was done, they turned back to the written deeds.

177
00:18:14,002 --> 00:18:18,926
[SPEAKER_11]: And that is where that language around the restriction sits.

178
00:18:19,847 --> 00:18:30,556
[SPEAKER_11]: So the SIRTE team was not aware of it themselves until end of February, early March is best we can ascertain from talking to Brennan.

179
00:18:32,173 --> 00:18:39,037
[SPEAKER_11]: However, in the meantime, we did learn from DCR, we've been having good communication coordination with DCR for the past two months.

180
00:18:39,657 --> 00:18:46,161
[SPEAKER_11]: DCR was the entity that brought this to the project team's attention on April 28th.

181
00:18:47,281 --> 00:18:56,286
[SPEAKER_11]: And of course, you're all well acquainted with the process of winnowing down the 29 PDP options to six in March.

182
00:18:56,806 --> 00:18:58,027
[SPEAKER_11]: You saw some development.

183
00:18:58,707 --> 00:19:02,309
[SPEAKER_11]: of those six options at the meeting on April 27th.

184
00:19:03,949 --> 00:19:08,852
[SPEAKER_11]: But of course, now that affects those options that you last saw in April.

185
00:19:09,872 --> 00:19:26,440
[SPEAKER_11]: So the three options that are not affected by the restriction are A1, the code upgrade, essentially the bounds of the existing building, B1.2, and D1.1, which builds on the southern portion of the site.

186
00:19:28,542 --> 00:19:53,071
[SPEAKER_11]: next and then the three that do impinge on restricted areas are c 2.2 c 3.4 and d 2.1 which is you know so what the team has done since and also informed by what we heard between meeting last monday of strong preference

187
00:19:53,724 --> 00:19:59,806
[SPEAKER_11]: for the C options, which allow you to keep your gym and pool and renovate them.

188
00:20:00,666 --> 00:20:12,409
[SPEAKER_11]: We've gone back to the drawing board, literally, and worked with those two C options to modify them to work within the bounds, I'll call it.

189
00:20:13,269 --> 00:20:16,170
[SPEAKER_11]: And we'd like to show those to you this evening.

190
00:20:24,754 --> 00:20:31,339
[SPEAKER_02]: Before we move on, does anyone on the committee have any questions about the deed restriction before we look at these alternatives?

191
