[SPEAKER_06]: It's still pretty tight there.

330
00:33:11,752 --> 00:33:19,954
[SPEAKER_06]: We're not there really to make that happen, but at this level, it looks like it could work out there.

331
00:33:20,114 --> 00:33:24,316
[SPEAKER_06]: Last question before we move on from this one.

332
00:33:24,476 --> 00:33:32,858
[SPEAKER_06]: So earlier, I think in the fall, there was an aerial survey with Mark Porter.

333
00:33:34,747 --> 00:33:42,470
[SPEAKER_06]: I recall there was also like some kind of remote sensing to characterize the composition of the ground.

334
00:33:44,071 --> 00:33:50,754
[SPEAKER_06]: I know this new footprint occupies a parking lot and maybe some courtyard.

335
00:33:51,174 --> 00:34:03,719
[SPEAKER_06]: I wanted to ask if the soils there were characterized and already deemed suitable for any foundations and digging that would have to occur to find any rock.

336
00:34:04,184 --> 00:34:06,705
[SPEAKER_06]: What were your findings in these new areas?

337
00:34:08,505 --> 00:34:17,688
[SPEAKER_10]: I think generally the soil is as suitable as the other soils on both of these building areas.

338
00:34:17,788 --> 00:34:29,492
[SPEAKER_10]: Once we have a preferred alternative, we head into schematic design, we may supplement these geotechnical explorations with additional borings or what have you based on where the actual building is going to go to confirm our assumptions.

339
00:34:30,166 --> 00:34:35,809
[SPEAKER_10]: But I'd say for all intents and purposes, soil conditions are about the same in both of these.

340
00:34:36,790 --> 00:34:49,077
[SPEAKER_06]: I think what's valid, right, is that generally across the site, about four to six feet down, you hit rock almost everywhere, aside from that area that's under the B wing, towards the front that used to be a quarry and sort of a trash dump historically.

341
00:34:49,897 --> 00:34:51,718
[SPEAKER_06]: And so that's where it goes deeper.

342
00:34:52,599 --> 00:34:58,722
[SPEAKER_06]: I think one of the nice things about this option and the C3 bullet bar option, as we move away from that deep restricted area,

343
00:34:59,135 --> 00:35:01,576
[SPEAKER_06]: we actually move away from the hillside and the rock.

344
00:35:01,676 --> 00:35:12,578
[SPEAKER_06]: So there should be less cost and less effort associated as we pull away from, say, the football practice field, and we're building up in the lower portion of ground as a boat that didn't get itself into that.

