[SPEAKER_06]: So this is just the first iteration of this activity for this project as we've gone through.

932
01:25:11,117 --> 01:25:19,364
[SPEAKER_06]: We did get the comments from the MSBA on 5-5, so May 5th, which I think was two Tuesdays before.

933
01:25:20,565 --> 01:25:24,689
[SPEAKER_06]: And we're given 10 business days to respond, so a total of two weeks.

934
01:25:24,769 --> 01:25:29,253
[SPEAKER_06]: And we did respond yesterday to sort of stay within that timeframe of what they were looking for.

935
01:25:30,494 --> 01:25:36,680
[SPEAKER_06]: When the MSBA provides those comments to us, they group their comments into two different documents, Attachment A and Attachment B.

936
01:25:37,783 --> 01:25:42,686
[SPEAKER_06]: Attachment A is sort of like the catch all for all the majority of their comments.

937
01:25:42,746 --> 01:25:53,312
[SPEAKER_06]: And they're looking at everything there from budget topics to anywhere they are.

938
01:25:54,353 --> 01:25:58,275
[SPEAKER_06]: Schedule comments, coordination between the end plan and the space summary.

939
01:25:59,493 --> 01:26:06,936
[SPEAKER_06]: as well as any items or statements that we need to be including within the PSR submission.

940
01:26:06,976 --> 01:26:16,720
[SPEAKER_06]: They ask for a lot of acknowledgements of their rules and regulations, and that's all part of attachment A. Attachment B is specifically comments on the space summary.

941
01:26:17,240 --> 01:26:27,003
[SPEAKER_06]: And that's interesting and important because what they do there is they start to give the district an idea of what spaces may be reimbursable and may not be reimbursable.

942
01:26:27,183 --> 01:26:28,504
[SPEAKER_06]: So when we start talking about

943
01:26:29,198 --> 01:26:33,360
[SPEAKER_06]: the city of Medford's reimbursement percentage overall and what that dollar value is.

944
01:26:33,780 --> 01:26:39,262
[SPEAKER_06]: It's the first insight that we get into MSBA's thinking on those particular topics.

945
01:26:39,663 --> 01:26:42,904
[SPEAKER_06]: What they give us at this first stage is not final by any means.

946
01:26:43,324 --> 01:26:47,566
[SPEAKER_06]: It's really an initial sense of what might be there from a reimbursable standpoint.

947
01:26:47,906 --> 01:26:56,730
[SPEAKER_06]: And there will be additional feedback and conversations that we have at the subsequent PSR submission, and then going all the way forward to schematic design, which is when all those things are locked in.

948
01:26:57,936 --> 01:27:14,962
[SPEAKER_06]: That's the general breakdown between attachment A and B. Just to note that the educational plan is going to be modified in some cases by the responses that were provided as part of the PDP comments in this process that we went through.

949
01:27:15,262 --> 01:27:19,564
[SPEAKER_06]: We don't provide the updated educational plan until we submit the PSR.

950
01:27:20,024 --> 01:27:22,885
[SPEAKER_06]: And at that point, it's a very prescriptive approach.

951
01:27:22,965 --> 01:27:27,507
[SPEAKER_06]: They want a red marked version so they can see the changes that are there, but they also want a final finish

952
01:27:28,310 --> 01:27:29,491
[SPEAKER_06]: that does not show any changes.

953
01:27:29,551 --> 01:27:33,473
[SPEAKER_06]: So that will be sort of the formal ed plan moving forward in the process.

954
01:27:34,414 --> 01:27:42,999
[SPEAKER_06]: And then one comment that the MSB also made, and I'm not sure if this is what Luke was alluding to earlier, was that they requested a school only cost option be provided.

955
01:27:43,899 --> 01:27:50,963
[SPEAKER_06]: And so that's really what they're asking for is something that just represents the grades nine to 12 school related programs.

956
01:27:51,884 --> 01:27:55,726
[SPEAKER_06]: So not say the district offices or other programs that are here,

957
01:27:56,265 --> 01:28:03,450
[SPEAKER_06]: and not necessarily the preschool program as well that would be brought here from outside the actual building.

958
01:28:04,911 --> 01:28:11,255
[SPEAKER_06]: So that particular request is not something that was challenging for us to respond to in terms of creating.

959
01:28:11,956 --> 01:28:15,298
[SPEAKER_06]: We actually have to provide them a specific submittal on that.

960
01:28:15,638 --> 01:28:21,502
[SPEAKER_06]: I think by the end of this week or Monday of next week, which is Memorial Day, so we're just going to get it to them by the end of this week.

961
01:28:22,150 --> 01:28:29,752
[SPEAKER_06]: But it's essentially taking all those program alternates that we already had included in the PDP cost estimate and that we repeated in the PSR cost estimate.

962
01:28:30,052 --> 01:28:30,872
[SPEAKER_06]: We just pulled those out.

963
01:28:31,052 --> 01:28:33,493
[SPEAKER_06]: And then that is the option that the MSBA is looking for.

964
01:28:34,193 --> 01:28:43,896
[SPEAKER_06]: So that level of transparency and information that they just want to make sure is clear for everybody in the community was really already cooked into how we were estimating things.

965
01:28:44,376 --> 01:28:48,057
[SPEAKER_06]: And so we're just pulling it out at their request so it can be viewed a little bit more easily.

966
01:28:51,451 --> 01:28:55,973
[SPEAKER_06]: And then attachment B, again, is the comments on the space summary.

967
01:28:57,033 --> 01:29:09,018
[SPEAKER_06]: They did ask us, in some cases, to shift spaces around between the different space categories, which is generally just a sign that they're looking to have something designated as reimbursable space versus non-reimbursable space.

968
01:29:09,038 --> 01:29:12,899
[SPEAKER_06]: That's really the intent behind shifts that we're asked to be doing.

969
01:29:13,959 --> 01:29:19,662
[SPEAKER_06]: And then the space summary, we did include an updated version as part of the responses.

970
01:29:21,222 --> 01:29:28,484
[SPEAKER_06]: The only changes in the version that we've provided as part of the comment and response were the updates that were made at the April 27 school building committee meeting.

971
01:29:28,804 --> 01:29:34,245
[SPEAKER_06]: The last time this group got together to reduce some spaces out just we want to provide that update to the MSBA.

972
01:29:35,066 --> 01:29:43,388
[SPEAKER_06]: And then we will submit the space summary again with the PSR report that will actually include all the revisions made that were in the comment responses.

973
01:29:43,468 --> 01:29:45,188
[SPEAKER_06]: If they ask us to do something we will do it.

974
01:29:45,248 --> 01:29:47,649
[SPEAKER_06]: We'll make those changes in the space summary and give it back to them.

975
01:29:49,018 --> 01:29:52,581
[SPEAKER_06]: And then just a word about the process in terms of these comments.

976
01:29:53,002 --> 01:30:02,470
[SPEAKER_06]: It's not a lot of time to actually orchestrate the responses to, I don't know how many pages we had in terms of comments before they ran in, maybe 26 different pages.

977
01:30:02,490 --> 01:30:03,571
[SPEAKER_06]: A lot.

978
01:30:03,711 --> 01:30:08,856
[SPEAKER_06]: The size and the quantity of the comments is really commensurate with the size and the complexity of the project.

979
01:30:08,896 --> 01:30:10,237
[SPEAKER_06]: And this is a large, complex project.

980
01:30:10,635 --> 01:30:15,697
[SPEAKER_06]: So it wasn't we were we're not under the impression that we would just be getting like five pages of comments back for this.

981
01:30:16,397 --> 01:30:19,438
[SPEAKER_06]: So that is sort of typical for our experience working through these.

982
01:30:20,538 --> 01:30:25,299
[SPEAKER_06]: Really the comments that we're dealing with the educational plan were answered by the district.

983
01:30:25,760 --> 01:30:33,962
[SPEAKER_06]: We are working with Dr. Talbot, Dr. Pelosi and their entire teams in terms of pulling in other involved parties if it's a director

984
01:30:34,833 --> 01:30:39,154
[SPEAKER_06]: or some other sort of curriculum question, we actually went to the content expert on that particular topic.

985
01:30:39,894 --> 01:30:42,195
[SPEAKER_06]: But those responses were written by the district.

986
01:30:42,575 --> 01:30:48,116
[SPEAKER_06]: There were some that were more related to sort of the mechanics and the logistics of the submission.

987
01:30:48,776 --> 01:30:52,577
[SPEAKER_06]: And so left field and SMA teamed up to provide those responses.

988
01:30:52,597 --> 01:30:57,818
[SPEAKER_06]: There was a collective response and review process from all three groups as we went through it.

989
01:30:58,334 --> 01:31:00,436
[SPEAKER_06]: I just wanted to reinforce that it's a collaborative effort.

990
01:31:00,456 --> 01:31:04,418
[SPEAKER_06]: It is not an SOMA just writing out all the answers and sending it off to the MSBA.

991
01:31:04,799 --> 01:31:15,266
[SPEAKER_06]: It's something that was really a collaborative spirit, just as the educational plan was, as we were putting it together, and just as the rest of the documentation being put together was collaborative.

992
01:31:16,507 --> 01:31:18,629
[SPEAKER_06]: And yes, it did go back yesterday.

993
01:31:19,309 --> 01:31:21,491
[SPEAKER_06]: So that's really the overall summary.

994
01:31:22,216 --> 01:31:32,063
[SPEAKER_06]: I know that the comments themselves, the responses were distributed out to the building committees so that you can see all the individual comments that were submitted and the responses to them.

995
01:31:34,684 --> 01:31:35,445
[SPEAKER_08]: Are there any questions?

996
01:31:35,905 --> 01:31:36,285
[SPEAKER_08]: Luke?

997
01:31:37,646 --> 01:31:43,570
[SPEAKER_06]: So if you want to commend the team on a thorough job, there was a lot to get through.

998
01:31:43,890 --> 01:31:44,791
[SPEAKER_06]: And I cheated.

999
01:31:44,911 --> 01:31:46,052
[SPEAKER_06]: I used a death notice.

1000
01:31:51,415 --> 01:32:02,863
[SPEAKER_06]: So, but I did want to make a kind of a statement, and this is more philosophical, like 30,000 foot, we're in a three way constraint problem.

1001
01:32:03,244 --> 01:32:14,912
[SPEAKER_06]: One is the MSPAA, I think you want scope, discipline, and it's obviously partial feedback, shared yesterday, more on that later.

1002
01:32:16,134 --> 01:32:21,738
[SPEAKER_06]: Another constraint are, I'll say, community advocates who want expansive civic functions.

1003
01:32:22,698 --> 01:32:29,323
[SPEAKER_06]: And then the third constraint that will emerge is taxpayer affordability.

1004
01:32:29,563 --> 01:32:31,404
[SPEAKER_06]: And we'll hear more about it next week.

1005
01:32:31,825 --> 01:32:38,429
[SPEAKER_06]: These terms and quantities data that are relevant to that.

1006
01:32:38,729 --> 01:32:44,953
[SPEAKER_06]: And we'll learn whether they support the full vision of, I'll say,

1007
01:32:47,258 --> 01:32:54,859
[SPEAKER_06]: The current PDP response package shows the district is trying to hold these three equities together simultaneously.

1008
01:32:55,980 --> 01:33:02,321
[SPEAKER_06]: Whether that remains sustainable is probably the defining question of summer and fall.

1009
01:33:02,701 --> 01:33:15,043
[SPEAKER_06]: As an SBC, I think we're approaching a critical moment where we'll need to determine whether this project evolves into a four-dimensional, fundable high school project with strong MSBA support and participation.

1010
01:33:15,789 --> 01:33:23,395
[SPEAKER_06]: or a larger civic campus concept that may incur a historically high local responsibility.

1011
01:33:24,756 --> 01:33:31,702
[SPEAKER_06]: The majority of this SBC has not seen approval from feedback from the MSBA, and I ask that we all see it.

1012
01:33:33,463 --> 01:33:43,531
[SPEAKER_06]: We've seen attachment A and B, and from what I can tell, there's at least a cover letter as well, cited in attachment A.

1013
01:33:44,211 --> 01:33:45,472
[SPEAKER_06]: Yeah, it's cited in tax review.

1014
01:33:45,492 --> 01:33:48,133
[SPEAKER_06]: There may be other things.

1015
01:33:48,193 --> 01:33:50,054
